  "text": "Furthermore, ABPM provided important information regarding BP loads in our patients. Although 25% of patients were diagnosed with hypertension by casual-BPs and mean ABPM BPs, a larger proportion of children had elevated systolic and diastolic loads (42 and 46%, respectively), suggesting suboptimal BP control. In a similar study of 12 children on chronic hemodialysis, Sorof [CITATION_1] found similarly elevated 24-hour SBP (35%) and DBP (36%) loads. Interestingly, our study also showed a markedly higher prevalence of elevated loads at night time (SBP: 58%; DBP: 71%).",
